================================================================================
META — Simulation Study Overview
================================================================================
Title : The impact of differential exposure measurement error on the
        PM2.5 -- preterm birth association: A simulation study
Author: Vijay Kumar
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Create true datasets
  Run CreateDataFinal.R from the project root. This generates:
    - truedta_null_Final.csv   (null association, true RR = 1.00)
    - truedta_ass_Final.csv    (harmful association, true RR = 1.115)

STEP 2 — Experiments
  Three experiments are provided, each in its own exp_00X subfolder.
  Each experiment repeats the same 10 simulation scenarios with a different
  error mean structure (see experiment descriptions below).

STEP 3 — Run simulations
  From inside the relevant exp_00X folder, either:
    (a) Run Sims_all.R in one screen session (~10-12 hrs, Mac M2 / 16 GB RAM)
    (b) Run sims1.R through sims10.R each in a separate screen session
        (~2.5 hrs total when run in parallel)

    (c)  Run scenarios individually in parallel using .sh file (~2.5 hrs total) --
        cd ~/Downloads/CodeReview/CodeReview_Heather
        chmod +x run_all_sims.sh   # only first time
        ./run_all_sims.sh # creates 10 screens named simsX and executes each simsX.R in that screen
        screen -ls # to check if all screens created and are running
        
    See the project-root readme for full screen session instructions.
================================================================================

STEP 4 — Visualize results
  Run VisualizeResults.R from inside each exp_00X/Results/ folder.
  This generates Figure 2, Figure 3, and data for Tables A3-A5.

  Run CI_check.Rmd from the project root (handles all three experiments).
  This generates Tables A1-A2 (Var_Corr.csv in each Results/ folder).

================================================================================
EXPERIMENT DESCRIPTIONS
================================================================================

exp_001 (E1): Random error only
  Error structure: v ~ N(mean = 0, sigma^2)
  The error mean is zero for all births and all scenarios.
  This is the baseline experiment representing pure classical measurement error.

exp_002 (E2): Random error with positive systematic shift
  Error structure: v ~ N(mean = +0.25, sigma^2)
  A positive shift of c = +0.25 per 1 unit of PM2.5 (equivalently +2.5 per
  10 units) is added to the error mean for at-risk (preterm) births.
  This models systematic over-assignment of exposure in high-risk individuals.

exp_003 (E3): Random error with negative systematic shift
  Error structure: v ~ N(mean = -0.25, sigma^2)
  A negative shift of c = -0.25 per 1 unit of PM2.5 (equivalently -2.5 per
  10 units) is added to the error mean for at-risk (preterm) births.
  This models systematic under-assignment of exposure in high-risk individuals.

